y''+k^2y=R(x)
y_1
y_1=\frac{1}{k}\int_0^x R(t)\sin(k(x-t))dt
y=C_1\sin kx+C_2\cos kx+\dfrac{\sin kx}{k}\int_0^xR(t)\cos kt~dt-\dfrac{\cos kx}{k}\int_0^xR(t)\sin kt~dt
y=C_1\sin kx+C_2\cos kx+\dfrac{1}{k}\int_0^xR(t)(\sin kx\cos kt-\cos kx\sin kt)~dt
y=C_1\sin kx+C_2\cos kx+\dfrac{1}{k}\int_0^xR(t)\sin(k(x-t))~dt
y_1=\dfrac{1}{k}\int_0^xR(t)\sin(k(x-t))~dt
